init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the â€œLost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The Lost Generations is a story about the lives of the people who were denied immortality, and how they cope with their lives.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The story is told through the eyes of a man who is 28 and is part of the Lost Generations.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: William is a man who is happy with his life and is content with his decision not to receive immortality.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: William has seen people who have taken the drug and have gone insane and have committed suicide.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: that people have become extremely obese and have been unable to move.
